1. The statement incorrectly assumes that only 5 percent of costs are related to transaction processing and routine accounting activities, when in fact, these activities consume about 69 percent of costs within finance according to the 1995 Financial Executives Research Foundation report.
2. Eliminating just 5 percent of processing would not significantly impact the overall financial operations, whereas eliminating the 69 percent of costs associated with transaction processing and routine accounting activities would have a major disruptive effect on financial operations.